result.name: AZIZA

reviews.text: Easily one of the best restaurants in Kennedy Town. Good authentic food and friendly customer service. I loved the lamb rack which comes with salad and rice. I also had the lamb shank to share with two other people. It is a tiny establishment so it may not be easy getting seats on busy nights or lunchtime. You can order through Food Panda though! 🤗

Disappointed. Pricey and small portions, especially rice and sauce. Taste is okay. I requested for "a little more sauce", they charged it without mentioning and 1/4 the price of the entire meal. Came in for a 90$ lunch set and ended up paying 121$ with a little extra sauce and service charge. Not worth it in my opinion.

Really good food - loved their hummus and Pita bread.  Fair portions and good to share.  Place is small and a bit cramped and a bit inconvenient to get to if you don’t know you’re way around Hong Kong. Definitely will return if I’m in HK and in the mood for Middle Eastern food.
Small but cozy restaurant. Very Friendly. Egyptian food is delicious, especially those grill and tagine. Must eat.
Great real middle East food run by an Egyptian family. Home made pita bread, great falafel...

result.name: Tapaella Grill

reviews.text:
Nice food and service. Set lunch is very value for money.  

Date of visit: 24 July 2019

Set lunch is decent and not expensive and the pasta dishes are delicious.  Highly recommend seafood pasta, protion is big, and lots of seafood in it.  So yummy....  Their lunch is served with salad or soup, coffee or dessert.  We have chosen ham salad, they use jamon as ham, impressive.

Only there is room of improvement is the aircon, every time when we dine there, we feel hot, especially when it is full house, it is indeed stuffy.
Very good seafood try the seafood paella and pil pil prawns
great food. good value
Good value, old school. Reasonably authentic Spanish. Great service. Very healthy sized glasses of wine!
